I can’t believe that Mysteries of Thorn Manor is only a week away! I also can’t believe it’s been over three and a half years since Sorcery of Thorns was published. Right now I’m feeling deeply grateful to my readers for remaining invested in these characters after so much time has passed. Your enthusiasm has helped them live on in my heart and mind, and it’s safe to say that if it weren’t for you, this novella wouldn’t exist. Going on this journey with you has been the adventure of a lifetime. Sincerely, thank you! 

Lately I’ve been getting a lot of questions about whether I will tell more stories in the Sorcery of Thorns world. Nothing official is forthcoming, but I have a lot of ideas about what might happen next for Elisabeth, Nathaniel, and Silas. It would mean the world to me if you considered preordering a copy of Thorn Manor, which will help let my publisher know that there’s continued interest in this world. If you live in the US and would like a signed/personalized copy, a great place to order one is through @cincybookshelf (just mention what you would like in the comment box at checkout).

If you’re curious about which editions of Sorcery are featured in this post, they are, from top to bottom:

